Cook 250 ml water per persoon in a #pot met deksel{} and cook the @zilvervliesrijst{170%g}, covered, ~{12-15%minutes}. Drain if necessary and let steam off uncovered.

Heat a #wok met deksel{} or #hapjespan{} on high heat and roast the @sesamzaad{20%g}, without oil, until golden brown. Remove from the pan and set aside. Chop the @gezouten cashewnoten{40%g} coarsely.

Cut the @peen{1}(in small cubes). Remove the stem end of the @sperziebonen{200%g} and cut into 2 equal pieces. Chop the @knoflookteen{2}(finely minced). Peel the @verse gember{2%cm} and chop finely. Slice the @bosui{4}(finely sliced) and keep the white and green part separate.

Heat half of the @olijfolie{1%el} in the same wok or hapjespan on medium-high heat and fry the carrots, stirring for ~{5%minutes}. Season with @peper{naar smaak} and @zout{naar smaak}. Add the green beans and fry, stirring, for ~{8-10%minutes}, or until the beans are tender. Remove from the pan and set aside. Meanwhile, heat the @zonnebloemolie{1%el} in a #koekenpan{} and fry 1 @ei{1} per person.

Wipe the wok or hapjespan clean with #keukenpapier{}. Heat the remaining @olijfolie{1%el} in the wok or hapjespan on medium-high heat. Add the garlic and ginger and fry for ~{1%minute}. Add the rice to the pan and fry, stirring, for ~{1-2%minutes}, until the rice is crispy and brown in color. Add the fried vegetables, half of the @sojasaus{10%ml}, and the white part of the spring onion and fry for ~{1%minute}. Taste and add more @sojasaus{10%ml} if desired.

Divide the rice over the #kommen{}. Serve with the fried egg and garnish with the cashew nuts, sesame seeds, and the green part of the spring onion.